#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (_pācittiya_)"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:0.4"
msgid "Musāvādavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 4"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:0.5"
msgid "4. Padasodhammasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on memorizing the Teaching"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-cs-bu-pc4.1, pts-vp-en.2.190, ms2V_150
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū upāsake padaso dhammaṃ vācenti."
msgstr "At that time the monks from the group of six were instructing lay followers to memorize the Teaching."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:1.3"
msgid "Upāsakā bhikkhūsu agāravā appatissā asabhāgavuttikā viharanti."
msgstr "Those lay followers became disrespectful, undeferential, and rude towards the monks."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: ms2V_151
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:1.4"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:1.5"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:1.6"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū upāsake padaso dhammaṃ vācessanti."
msgstr "“How can the monks from the group of six instruct lay followers to memorize the Teaching,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:1.7"
msgid "Upāsakā bhikkhūsu agāravā appatissā asabhāgavuttikā viharantī”ti."
msgstr "those lay followers becoming disrespectful, undeferential, and rude towards the monks?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:1.8"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:1.9"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, upāsake padaso dhammaṃ vācetha;"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:1.10"
msgid "upāsakā bhikkhūsu agāravā appatissā asabhāgavuttikā viharantī”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:1.11"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:1.12"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:1.13"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, upāsake padaso dhammaṃ vācessatha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you instruct lay followers to memorize the Teaching,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:1.14"
msgid "Upāsakā bhikkhūsu agāravā appatissā asabhāgavuttikā viharanti."
msgstr "those lay followers becoming disrespectful, undeferential, and rude towards the monks?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:1.15"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya pasannānaṃ vā bhiyyobhāvāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it or increase the confidence of those who have it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:1.16"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:1.16a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc3, ms2V_152
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:1.17"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu anupasampannaṃ padaso dhammaṃ vāceyya pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk instructs a person who is not fully ordained to memorize the Teaching, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc4, pts-cs-bu-pc4.2.1, ms2V_153
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti "
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe … ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc5, pts-vp-en.2.191, ms2V_154
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.1.5"
msgid "Anupasampanno nāma"
msgstr "A person who is not fully ordained:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.1.6"
msgid "bhikkhuñca bhikkhuniñca ṭhapetvā avaseso anupasampanno nāma."
msgstr "anyone except a fully ordained monk and a fully ordained nun."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc6, pts-vp-pli4.15, ms2V_155
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.1.7"
msgid "Padaso nāma"
msgstr "To memorize:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.1.8"
msgid "padaṃ, anupadaṃ, anvakkharaṃ, anubyañjanaṃ."
msgstr "a line, the next line, syllable by syllable, the next phrase."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc7, ms2V_156
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.1.9"
msgid "Padaṃ nāma"
msgstr "A line:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.1.10"
msgid "ekato paṭṭhapetvā ekato osāpenti."
msgstr "they start together and finish together."

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.1.11"
msgid "Anupadaṃ nāma"
msgstr "The next line:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.1.12"
msgid "pāṭekkaṃ paṭṭhapetvā ekato osāpenti."
msgstr "one of them starts, but they finish together."

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.1.13"
msgid "Anvakkharaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Syllable by syllable:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.1.14"
msgid "“rūpaṃ aniccan”ti vuccamāno, “run”ti opāteti."
msgstr "when ‘_rūpaṃ aniccaṃ_’ is being said, he prompts him, saying, ‘_rū_.’"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.1.15"
msgid "Anubyañjanaṃ nāma"
msgstr "The next phrase:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.1.16"
msgid "“rūpaṃ aniccan”ti vuccamāno, “vedanā aniccā”ti saddaṃ nicchāreti."
msgstr "when ‘_rūpaṃ aniccaṃ_,’ is being said, the other says, ‘_vedanā aniccā_.’"

#. HTML: </span></p><p>
#. REF: sc8, ms2V_157
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.1.17"
msgid "Yañca padaṃ, yañca anupadaṃ, yañca anvakkharaṃ, yañca anubyañjanaṃ—"
msgstr "And whatever line there is, whatever next line, whatever syllable by syllable, whatever next phrase—"

#. VAR: padaso → padaso dhammo (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.1.18"
msgid "sabbametaṃ padaso nāma."
msgstr "this is all called “to memorize the Teaching.”"

#. HTML: </p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms2V_158
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.1.19"
msgid "Dhammo nāma"
msgstr "The Teaching:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.192
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.1.20"
msgid "buddhabhāsito, sāvakabhāsito, isibhāsito, devatābhāsito, atthūpasañhito, dhammūpasañhito."
msgstr "what has been spoken by the Buddha, what has been spoken by disciples, what has been spoken by sages, what has been spoken by gods, what is connected with what is beneficial, what is connected with the Teaching."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc10, ms2V_159
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.1.21"
msgid "Vāceyyāti"
msgstr "Instructs:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.1.22"
msgid "padena vāceti, pade pade āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "if he instructs by the line, then for every line he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.1.23"
msgid "Akkharāya vāceti, akkharakkharāya āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If he instructs by the syllable, then for every syllable he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc11, pts-cs-bu-pc4.2.2, ms2V_160
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.2.1"
msgid "Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī padaso dhammaṃ vāceti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is a person who is not fully ordained, and the monk perceives them as not fully ordained, and he instructs them to memorize the Teaching, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.2.2"
msgid "Anupasampanne vematiko padaso dhammaṃ vāceti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is a person who is not fully ordained, but the monk is unsure of it, and he instructs them to memorize the Teaching, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.2.3"
msgid "Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī padaso dhammaṃ vāceti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is a person who is not fully ordained, but the monk perceives them as fully ordained, and he instructs them to memorize the Teaching, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12, ms2V_161
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.2.4"
msgid "Upasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is a person who is fully ordained, but the monk perceives them as not fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.2.5"
msgid "Upasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is a person who is fully ordained, but the monk is unsure if they are, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.2.6"
msgid "Upasampanne upasampannasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it is a person who is fully ordained, and the monk perceives them as fully ordained, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc13, pts-cs-bu-pc4.2.3, ms2V_162
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.3.2"
msgid "ekato uddisāpento,"
msgstr "if he causes a recitation together;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.3.3"
msgid "ekato sajjhāyaṃ karonto,"
msgstr "if they practice together;"

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.193
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.3.4"
msgid "yebhuyyena paguṇaṃ ganthaṃ bhaṇantaṃ opāteti,"
msgstr "if he prompts one who is speaking a mostly familiar text;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.3.5"
msgid "osārentaṃ opāteti,"
msgstr "if he prompts one who is reciting;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.3.6"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.3.7"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc14, ms2V_163
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:2.3.8"
msgid "Padasodhammasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ."
msgstr "The fourth rule, the training rule on memorizing the Teaching, is finished."
